Ethical Considerations
Data See §H.1for data annotation card
Cost and impact of compute The released SAM 3 was trained on 172k A100 GPU hours and 86k H200 GPU
hours. This corresponds to an estimated 142k-176k kWH and emissions between
65.3 and 77.6 metric tons of CO2e (Patterson et al., 2021 ;Lacoste et al., 2019 ).
The emissions from training the released SAM 3 model are equivalent to 166k miles
driven by an average gasoline-powered passenger vehicle (Agency, 2022 ).
Risks and harms The behavior of SAM 3 is undefined for opinionated or subjective queries (e.g.
magnificent painting) and should not be used to make subjective judgments about
objects or people. Users should evaluate the safety of SAM 3 tailored to their
specific use case.
Use cases We implore users to use their best judgment.
